    "(60)Deviations from this result would signal non SM operators in the effective Hamiltonian or/and modified values of the Wilson coefficients.",
    "Another observableA (2) T (q 2) = 2S 3 (q 2) 1 -F L (q 2) (61)is sensitive to the virtual photon polarization [60,61], which in SM is mainly left-handed, the right-handed polarization being suppressed by m s /m b. Deviations are expected in scenarios where the photon can also be right-handed, an effect encoded in the operator O ′ 7, which is not generated in the scenario A of the ABCD model.",
    "LFV lepton decaysIn this section we examine the contribution of Z ′ to LFV leptonic modes.",
    "We begin with the processes µ -→ e -γ, τ -→ µ -µ + µ -and µ -→ e -e + e -.",
    "In absence of neutrino oscillations such processes do not occur in SM."
